[00:00.34]	[Hall in Capulet's house.,]
[00:01.04]	[Enter CAPULET, LADY CAPULET, Nurse, and two
[00:01.39]	+ Servingmen]
[00:01.73]CAPULET	So many guests invite as here are writ.
[00:04.34]	[Exit First Servant]
[00:05.03]	Sirrah, go hire me twenty cunning cooks.
[00:07.64]Second Servant	You shall have none ill, sir; for I'll try if they
[00:10.83]	can lick their fingers.
[00:12.51]CAPULET	How canst thou try them so?
[00:14.42]Second Servant	Marry, sir, 'tis an ill cook that cannot lick his
[00:17.49]	own fingers: therefore he that cannot lick his
[00:20.50]	fingers goes not with me.
[00:22.29]CAPULET	Go, be gone.
[00:23.28]	[Exit Second Servant]
[00:23.97]	We shall be much unfurnished for this time.
[00:26.81]	What, is my daughter gone to Friar Laurence?
[00:29.65]Nurse	Ay, forsooth.
[00:30.69]CAPULET	Well, he may chance to do some good on her:
